'''Oscar George Threlkeld''' (born 15 February 1994) is an English professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for {{English football updater|SalfordC}} club [[Salford City F.C.|Salford City]].

Originally a [[Defender_(association_football)#Centre-back|centre-half]], Threlkeld's versatility has also seen him play as a [[Defender_(association_football)#Full-back|full-back]] and a [[Midfielder#Defensive_midfielder|defensive midfielder]].

==Career==
===Bolton Wanderers===
Threkleld came through Bolton's [[Bolton Wanderers F.C. Reserves and Academy|academy]] and made his debut for the team on 26 April 2014 when he started in a 3–1 away win against [[Sheffield Wednesday F.C.|Sheffield Wednesday]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/27084131|title=Sheffield Wednesday 1–3 Bolton Wanderers|publisher=}}</ref> At the end of the 2015–16 season, the club confirmed that he would be leaving when his contract expired at the end of June.<ref>{{cite web|title=Bolton Wanderers confirm player departures|url=http://www.bwfc.co.uk/news/article/bolton-wanderers-confirm-player-departures-3112552.aspx|publisher=bwfc.co.uk|date=13 May 2016|accessdate=13 May 2016}}</ref>

===Plymouth Argyle===
On 27 August 2015, Threlkeld signed on loan for [[Plymouth Argyle F.C.|Plymouth Argyle]] until 2 January.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pafc.co.uk/news/article/oscar-buzz-2650839.aspx|title=Oscar Buzz|first=Rick|last=Cowdery|publisher=}}</ref> He made his debut for the club as an 83rd-minute substitute in a 3–2 win at [[AFC Wimbledon]] in the [[Football League Trophy]], replacing [[Gregg Wylde]].<ref>{{Cite news|title = AFC Wimbledon v Plymouth Argyle|url = https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/34048012|newspaper = BBC|accessdate = 2015-09-02}}</ref> He scored his first career goal in a 2–1 defeat in the [[West_Country_derby#Football|Devon derby]] against [[Exeter City F.C.|Exeter City]] on 21 November 2015.<ref>{{Cite news|title = Plymouth Argyle 1 Exeter City 2|url =https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/34817878|publisher = BBC|date = 21 November 2015|accessdate = 10 December 2018}}</ref> Threlkeld's loan expired in January 2016, but was promptly extended until the end of the regular season. The terms of his loan meant he was unable to play for Argyle in the [[2015–16_Football_League_Two#Play-offs|play-offs]] that season.<ref>{{Cite news|title = Argyle Act Fast and Keep Oscar|url =https://www.pafc.co.uk/news/2016/january/argyle-act-fast-and-keep-oscar/|publisher = PAFC|date = 6 January 2016|accessdate = 10 December 2018}}</ref>

Threlkeld was released by Bolton and on 2 July 2016 he was signed on a permanent deal by Argyle.<ref>{{Cite news|title= Oscar Sequel|url= https://www.pafc.co.uk/news/2016/july/oscar-sequel/|publisher= PAFC|date= 2 July 2016|accessdate= 10 December 2018}}</ref> [[2016–17 EFL League Two|That season]], Argyle won promotion from the [[EFL League Two]] as runners-up, with Threlkeld scoring two goals: in a 2–1 defeat away to [[Morecambe F.C.|Morecambe]]<ref>{{cite web|title=MORECAMBE VS. PLYMOUTH ARGYLE  2 - 1 |url=https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2016/11/26/england/league-two/morecambe-fc/plymouth-argyle-fc/2248057/|website=Soccerway|date=26 November 2016|accessdate=10 December 2018}}</ref>, and in a 2–0 win at home to [[Crawley Town F.C.|Crawley Town]].<ref>{{cite web|title=PLYMOUTH ARGYLE VS. CRAWLEY TOWN  2 - 0 |url=https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2016/12/31/england/league-two/plymouth-argyle-fc/crawley-town-football-club/2248105/ |website=Soccerway|date=31 December 2016|accessdate=10 December 2018}}</ref>

In the [[2017–18 Plymouth Argyle F.C. season|17-18 season]] Threlkeld made 26 appearances as Argyle missed out on the [[2017–18_EFL_League_One#Play-offs|League One play-offs]] by three points.

===Waasland-Beveren===
He was offered a new contract by Plymouth Argyle at the end of the 2017–18 season, <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44054754|title=Gary Sawyer: Plymouth Argyle offer new deal to captain as nine are released|date=9 May 2018|accessdate=9 May 2018|publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref> but he chose to reject the offer and sign a three-year deal with [[Belgian First Division A]] side [[Waasland-Beveren]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.waasland-beveren.be/2018/05/oscar-threlkeld-komt-geel-blauwe-rangen-versterken/|title=OSCAR THRELKELD KOMT DE GEEL-BLAUWE RANGEN VERSTERKEN!|language=Dutch|trans-title=OSCAR THRELKELD WILL JOIN THE YELLOW-BLUE RANKS!|date=15 May 2018|accessdate=12 July 2018|publisher=[[Waasland-Beveren]]}}</ref>

Threlkeld made his debut for Beveren on 3 August 2018 in a 0–0 draw with [[Standard Liège]], where he received a [[Fouls_and_misconduct_(association_football)#Yellow_card_(caution)|booking]] in the 90+3rd minute.<ref>{{cite web|title=O.Threlkeld |url=https://uk.soccerway.com/players/oscar-threlkeld/322038/|website=Soccerway|accessdate=10 December 2018}}</ref>

====Return to Argyle====
On 8 January 2019, Threlkeld rejoined [[Plymouth Argyle F.C.|Plymouth Argyle]] on a temporary deal until the end of the season, with him set to return to Beveren once the season had ended.<ref>{{cite news|first=Rick|last=Cowdery|title=Oscar Four - Bravo! |url=https://www.pafc.co.uk/news/2019/january/oscar-threlkeld-returns-to-argyle-on-loan/|website=Plymouth Argyle F.C.|date=8 January 2019|accessdate=8 January 2019}}</ref>

===Salford City===
He joined [[Salford City F.C.|Salford City]] on 3 June 2019 on a two-year contract.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://salfordcityfc.co.uk/oscar-threlkeld-signs-for-salford-city-030619/|title=Oscar Threlkeld signs for Salford City|publisher=Salford City FC|date=3 June 2019}}</ref>

